{
  "doc_id": "2895",
  "text": "A set of 80 pictures from the NimStim Face Stimulus Set [CITATION_1] were selected based on previously obtained self-report ratings of typicality, valence, and arousal (see procedure below). Our goal was to select facial stimuli that differed in their affective properties within emotional categories (e.g., pleasant and unpleasant surprised faces, low and high arousal angry faces) for typical and atypical actors.",
